---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title=About Me description=About Me />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1 style="text-align: center;"> About Me </h1>
			<p>
				I'm a final year student on the University of Edinburgh's MPhys Physics with Year Abroad course, which is a five-year integrated Masters where the student travels to a partner institute for their fourth year to complete a year of full-time academic research, replacing formal teaching. I chose to attend the University of Melbourne to perform astrophysical research, using convolutional neural networks to photometrically identify the oldest galaxies in the Universe. After this placement, I undertook a research internship with STFC/ROE measuring the chemical composition of different galaxies spectroscopically, looking for trends between composition and galaxy mass. For my Masters thesis, I derived a time-symmetric formulation for gravitational wave emission from particles and explored the resulting effect on their trajectories, as well as the necessity of boundary conditions set by the Big Bang. Throughout my degree I have become proficient in Python and have explored C++, and now I'm exploring HTML and CSS.
			</p>
		
			<p>
				Over the last five years I have tried to broaden my physics knowledge as much as possible - studying a suite of general physics courses, as well as specialising in galaxies and gravitational physics to expand my knowledge of these areas. Outside of my studies, I have enjoyed participating in the University of Edinburgh's rocketry team, endeavour, as well as the University of Melbourne's rocketry team, ARES. I have spent three years developing high-powered rocket airframes, and as a result I have been inspired to pursue a career in mechnical/aerospace engineering. 
			</p>
		
			<p>
				A general overview of my professional experience can be found on my LinkedIn profile - click the icon in the header or footer of this website to go there.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
